Jenna collects stamps.She puts the same number of stamps on each page and then inserts each page into one of her two stamp books.One of her stamp books has a total of 840 stamps.The other has 1008.
Let's say Jenna puts x stamps on each page. 
If she has a total of 840 stamps in one book, then the number of pages in that book would be 840 / x.
solution: The number of stamps Jenna puts on each page must divide the number of stamps she puts into each book, so the largest possible number of stamps she puts on each page is gcd$(840, 1008) = \boxed{168}$.
